OL,3,CRyanair mulls larger staff bonus for
OL,4,Ccatching passengers with oversized
OL,5,Cluggage
OL,7,FRyanair is considering increasing a
OL,8,Fbonus paid to staff for identifying
OL,9,Fpassengers' oversized luggage, its
OL,10,Fchief executive said.
OL,12,FThe airline currently pays staff
OL,13,Faround 1.50 euros (#1.30) for
OL,14,Fintercepting customers who are
OL,15,Fbringing larger-than-permitted bags
OL,16,Fonto the aircraft.
OL,18,FIt is reported that the bonus is
OL,19,Fcapped at about 80 euros (#70) for
OL,20,Feach staff member per month.
